                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A creature that takes damage from a Bastardhall rat's bite is exposed to a painful and debilitating curse, and must attempt a @Check[fortitude|dc:22] save against the following effects.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected by the curse.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> Pain shoots through the creature as angry redringed blisters form in the vicinity of the bite. The creature becomes @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 1} by the pain.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> As success, but @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 2}. In addition, the blisters linger even after the initial pain abates, leaving the creature @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Enfeebled]{Enfeebled 1} from the discomfort for as long as the curse persists. Each time the sun rises, the creature can attempt a @Check[fortitude|dc:22] save to end the curse's effects.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the curse has an unlimited duration, and its effects grow more discomforting after dark, increasing to @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Enfeebled]{Enfeebled 2} and @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 1} while the sun is down.</p>"
                },
